snippet: The 30-year-old, who was believed to have been pregnant, was sitting on a bench in Kissena Park, the police said, when the tree fell.
abstract: Tree falls in Kissena Park in Queens, killing a 30-year-old woman who was believed to have been pregnant; no information is available on what might have caused the tree to fall.
lead_paragraph: The 30-year-old, who was believed to have been pregnant, was sitting on a bench in Kissena Park, the police said, when the tree fell.

headline.main: Falling Tree Kills Woman in Queens
